    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Long mantles worn at formal but non-liturgical occasions. The color of the garment indicates the rank of the cleric, black for secular priests, purple for bishops, and scarlet for cardinals. The pope does not wear a ferraiolone.</Note_Text>
